cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG 

The paper deals with computer vision techniques for analysing social interactions from egocentric photostreams. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of clustering algorithms, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another likely category. The paper also discusses the correlation between social events, lifestyle, and health, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of wearable cameras, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the validation of the proposed model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
